article.description: Sam Dower scored 21 points, Elias Harris added 18 and Gonzaga moved into a first-place tie in the West Coast Conference with an 89-85 overtime victory over Saint Mary's on Thursday night.
article.headline: Gonzaga wins in OT to move into tie atop WCC
article.linkText: Gonzaga wins in OT to move into tie atop WCC
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. -- Sam Dower scored 21 points, Elias Harris added 18 and Gonzaga moved into a first-place tie in the West Coast Conference with an 89-85 overtime victory over Saint Mary's on Thursday night. The Bulldogs (20-9, 10-3) overcame a rowdy road crowd and held off the Gaels to keep alive their hopes of building on a decade of dominance in the conference. Gonzaga has won a share of the league's regular-season title each of the past 10 years and can claim at least a portion of it again with a win against San Diego on Saturday. Matthew Dellavedova had 24 points and Rob Jones scored 21 for Saint Mary's (22-7, 10-3), which has lost two straight conference games and will need a win over Portland this weekend to settle for at least a share of the conference crown. The Gaels could have won their first outright regular-season WCC championship since 1989 with a victory over Gonzaga. Instead, the Zags showed why they've been so dominant.
